cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.DL, cs.CY, cs.HC 

This paper deals with the ability of search engines to distinguish between documents in different languages, which is a common issue in information retrieval (IR). Therefore, cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves natural language processing (NLP) to some extent, as it deals with the ability of search engines to recognize different languages, which could fall under cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper involves analyzing search results, which could fall under cs.DL (Digital Libraries). The paper also has implications for cross-lingual communication and human-computer interaction, which could fall under cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction), respectively.
